The course gives an overview of the structure of different organism groups (e.g. animals, plants, mushrooms), their systems, biology, adaptation, spread and endangerment. Skills necessary for teachers are practised in seminars and practical lessons by using different study methods.Objectives/eesmärkid:  To introduce students to wildlife objects and phenomena related to them; to develop students' knowledge and skills of guiding children to notice, experience and explore the surrounding world.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  On completion of the course the student:
- knows the wildlife system and its diversity;
- uses various sources for searching topic-related information;
- explains the role of different organisms in the ecosystem and aspects related to their protection;
- chooses and uses appropriate methods, activities and forms of classroom work while teaching the topics related to biological diversity in a preschool educational institution.
